  "prompt": "Did Hillary Clinton break the law by using private e-mail for official business? Was she doing anything illegal?",
  "response": "The use of private email by Hillary Clinton during her tenure as Secretary of State has been a subject of significant controversy and investigation. In 2015, the State Department's Inspector General issued a report stating that Clinton's use of a private email account for official business was not in line with the department's policies at the time. \n\nThe FBI conducted an investigation into whether Clinton had mishandled classified information through her private email server. In July 2016, then-FBI Director James Comey announced that while Clinton and her team were \"extremely careless\" in handling classified information, the FBI did not recommend criminal charges against her. The rationale was that there was no evidence that she intended to violate the law or that her actions met the legal standard for prosecution.\n\nIn summary, while Clinton's use of a private email account was deemed inappropriate and not compliant with federal regulations, the investigations determined that she did not break the law in a prosecutable sense.",
